AS UBER prepares for its public listing this week, a new study shows that ride-hailing companies cause major road congestion in San Francisco. Also, how much should smart speakers see as well as hear? And Douglas Rushkoff, an author, explains why he thinks the internet and social media are harmful to humans. Kenneth Cukier hosts. Runtime: 20 min.    Listen on: Apple Podcasts | Spotify | Google | Stitcher | TuneIn